[1] 2) Checking normality assumption
[1] # Building the linear model
[1] # Creating a QQ plot of residuals
[1] ### Compute Shapiro-Wilk test of normality ###
# A tibble: 1 × 3
  variable         statistic  p.value
  <chr>                <dbl>    <dbl>
1 residuals(model)     0.689 5.13e-26
[1] The normality assumption is not supported by the Shapiro-Wilk test. The p-value is significant (p = 5.12529429745685e-26),
[1] so we cannot assume normality for this dataset.
[1] 
[1] 3) Checking homogeneity of variance assumption
[1] This can be checked using the Levene’s test:
# A tibble: 1 × 4
    df1   df2 statistic        p
  <int> <int>     <dbl>    <dbl>
1     5   378      12.8 1.82e-11
[1] The Levene’s test is not significant (p > 1.8217014423096e-11). Therefore, we can assume the homogeneity of variances in the different groups.
